1 (d) At the hearing, the following rights of the parties shall be preserved:
2 (1) The right to present sworn evidence, law, or rules that bear upon the case.
3 (2) The right to represent themselves or obtain the services of an attorney at their
4 own expense.
5 (3) The right to subpoena witnesses, cross-examine witnesses of the other party,
6 and make a closing argument summarizing the party's view of the case and
7 the law. The juvenile who was the subject of the abuse or serious neglect shall
