40 eligible for under the agreement.
41 (3) The procedure by which the guardian may apply for additional services as
42 needed.
43 (4) The State will pay the total cost of nonrecurring expenses associated with
44 obtaining legal guardianship of the child to the extent the total cost does not
45 exceed two thousand dollars ($2,000).
46 (c) A guardianship agreement entered into under this section shall provide that the
47 agreement shall remain in effect without regard to the State residency of the guardian.
48 "§ 108A-50.13. Reimbursement for guardians.
49 The guardianship assistance program rates shall reimburse legal and relative guardians for
50 room and board and be set at the same rate as the foster care room and board rates in accordance
51 with rates established under G.S. 108A-49.1."
